<br>
I think some of the better guilds that have formed have actually been from scratch, lower lvls who have developed over time. Remember not even god created the world in a day. He took his time, plotting things out over several days to fit the image he sought. So it should be with a guild, the trouble is patience is a virtue and to some they do not have patience or it could just be that because of limited game time to play so they would like to get on and instantly get into a raid. Which is understandable when your short on game time.<br>
<br>
It all boils down to, how willing and patient will you remain? On Mith marr I was able to help establish several low lvl guilds who as of late I went back to do a follow up on, they have become very powerful guilds now. Just takes time, Doofy, if you need a good guild I know several off hand who would be glad to have you in their ranks. Don't rush to be guilded to have that tag, some of the best players are not in guilds, so the myth of people not in guilds are &quot;bad&quot; players. Bah, just a myth. <br>
<br>
Time, it's very crucial part of the decision making and many other processes in a game and in life as a whole. <br>
<br>
